Dialogue: 10,0:01:31.46,0:01:33.23,Top,,0,0,0,,You've not much time! {?????????}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:33.23,0:01:34.78,Top,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.10,0:01:37.38,Top,,0,0,0,,Quick!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.70,0:01:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure you don't want me to see you off?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.84,0:01:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.04,0:01:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Give my regards to Miss Roberts.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.71,0:01:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Write to us soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.81,0:01:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! We're off!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.78,0:01:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi! Isabel, Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.65,0:01:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.95,0:02:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you, my dear twin cousins? \NI came to pick you up.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.46,0:02:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Came to pick us up?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.23,0:02:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.02,0:02:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be going to St. Clare's with you now.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:09.63,0:02:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:11.73,0:02:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? So my mum didn't tell yours?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:15.09,0:02:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, recently...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:17.77,0:02:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,she's been asking me all sorts of things about St. Clare's on the phone.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.07,0:02:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And starting this semester, \Nshe decided to send me there too.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:25.66,0:02:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is this happening to us?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.52,0:02:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, you'd really be better off \Ngoing to Ringmere!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.09,0:02:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that you must come where we go?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.86,0:02:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, Pat, take good care of your cousin.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.79,0:02:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you'll be reliable guides \Nthrough St. Clare's for her.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.62,0:02:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mustn't be concerned, uncle and aunt.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.90,0:02:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how to take care of myself, \Nno special babysitting needed.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.62,0:02:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.64,0:02:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Our fun new semester...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.54,0:02:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is getting messed up because of her?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.88,0:03:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Like we'll stand for it!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.88,0:03:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.06,0:03:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Change into your uniform \Nas soon as you arrive at the station.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.83,0:03:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.33,0:03:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts is going to get mad.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.60,0:03:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Over something like this?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.24,0:03:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't underestimate Miss Roberts's strictness.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.34,0:03:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be fine changing \Nwhen I get to school.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.79,0:03:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.46,0:03:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallo, twins!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:43.62,0:03:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen! Has Binks been behaving well since you brought him to your aunt's house?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.36,0:03:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He may have been a little too energetic, though—he gave auntie a shock!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.57,0:03:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you feel sad when it was time to leave?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.43,0:03:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sort of.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.66,0:04:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness me, twins! Did you become even prettier while I wasn't watching?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.99,0:04:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but shouldn't we be saying that? {lit: that kind of thing is precisely janet-sama}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.11,0:04:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all so much prettier now!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:05.95,0:04:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Clare's students bloom more\N with every break they take. {/become more beautiful}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.98,0:04:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But the only real progress we have \Nis with words, it seems. {lit: advancing is only mouth it seems - probably means that they talk more eloquently now?}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.29,0:04:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oi, girls, we brought someone along! {/let us introduce}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.03,0:04:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Our cousin Alison.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.06,0:04:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where did she go now?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.83,0:04:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your cousin will be changing schools?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.73,0:04:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.80,0:04:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.80,0:04:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Miss Roberts!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.70,0:04:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.40,0:04:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You all seem jolly well together.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.34,0:04:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.17,0:04:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, Pat, where is your cousin, Alison?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.68,0:04:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.52,0:04:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She was with us just a moment ago...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.95,0:04:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.34,0:04:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.55,0:04:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have you been?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:49.19,0:04:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to buy this.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.08,0:04:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.55,0:04:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Isabel, Pat? \NWon't you introduce me to the class?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.07,0:05:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And who's this old trout? {oba-sama - need to sound slightly disrespectful}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.15,0:05:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Old trout?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.17,0:05:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Miss Roberts!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.92,0:05:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Introduce yourself properly! {lit: say hello}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.68,0:05:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This pretty lady is our teacher?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.54,0:05:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Golly, that's a delight!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.91,0:05:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard a lot about you from Isabel and Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.45,0:05:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.82,0:05:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Alison O'Sullivan. \NMighty pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.76,0:05:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you. {/do your best}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.06,0:05:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Alison...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.36,0:05:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.36,0:05:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that outfit?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.59,0:05:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Golly! You like my outfit too? {/want to praise}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.80,0:05:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I was also considering a green jacket, \Nbut decided to go with this.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.20,0:05:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The new semester begins now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.01,0:05:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Change into your uniform at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.28,0:05:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? O-Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.41,0:05:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I was actually planning to change on the train.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.20,0:05:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Be prepared: St. Clare’s is well ahead of Ringmere School in their curriculum.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.66,0:06:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I'll manage, so rest easy.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.90,0:06:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Cleaning, laundry, mending our clothes—\Nwe do everything ourselves!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.38,0:06:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.60,0:06:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.77,0:06:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.59,0:06:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.64,0:06:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I do that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.88,0:06:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't we have maids for that kind of thing?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.88,0:06:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A girl your age should be able \Nto do that {\i1}at least{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.28,0:06:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,One should be embarrassed if she's not!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.09,0:06:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you laughing?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.07,0:06:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because not so long ago, \Nyou two talked the same way Alison does now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.03,0:06:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that sounds about right! {/isn't that so}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.25,0:06:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm still hungry...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.77,0:06:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right! That's what I brought a cake for. \NIt won't be cheap for you, though. {lit: I'll sell it to anyone who wants it}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.34,0:06:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Just kidding!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.35,0:06:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.22,0:06:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So-so.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.35,0:06:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey you, the girl in the isle!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.65,0:07:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.52,0:07:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You're a newcomer, aren't you?\NWhat's your name? {they're technically in second year now i think so "freshman" doesn't work, right?}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.17,0:07:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison O'Sullivan.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.83,0:07:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison? Can't you keep it quiet?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.66,0:07:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Me? But I wasn't particularly loud already.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.10,0:07:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, we’ve got a shovelful of French homework to get through, so we’re cramming like mad right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.37,0:07:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.69,0:07:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So what...?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.18,0:07:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your loud bawling is both distracting \Nand a thorough nuisance!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.05,0:07:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to stay quiet.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.71,0:07:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't have been slacking off \Nduring vacations. {meaning "that's your fault for not doing your homework earlier" - she's not wrong though}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.46,0:07:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.46,0:07:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.45,0:07:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We've no time for that! \NWe need to finish our homework!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.46,0:07:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That person is Rita George.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.23,0:07:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She's so scary even most of the seniors \Nprefer not to get in her way. {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.27,0:07:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, I'm scared!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.47,0:07:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be more careful.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.07,0:07:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She might even summon you later.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.24,0:07:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Summon?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.61,0:07:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, look...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.68,0:08:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If that’s all there is to being summoned, \Nit’s a piece of cake!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.70,0:08:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? {/why}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.85,0:08:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because even if I wanted to, I haven’t the faintest idea how to light the stove or polish the shoes.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.72,0:08:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It’d be no use asking me to do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.66,0:08:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's also exactly the kind of thing \NIsabel and Pat used to say!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.46,0:08:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because everyone at Redroofs is like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.10,0:08:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're not at Redroofs any more. {lit: now it's different}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.87,0:08:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll also have to work hard now.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.24,0:08:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Work hard?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.07,0:08:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To think I'd hear such a thing \Nfrom the O'Sullivan twins, of all people!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.29,0:08:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Not quite how I expected this place to be.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.02,0:08:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems fine so far.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.86,0:08:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.09,0:08:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to understand, Alison.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.46,0:08:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't start taking seriously what we say, \Nwe won't be able to help you! {???? no idea what's that kamatte agenai, probably means "we'll stop looking after you"?}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.94,0:08:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's Matron!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.50,0:08:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, Pat, how was it? \NDid you enjoy your vacation?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.28,0:08:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.47,0:09:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, we brought our cousin along. {??? think I hear "entering our school this year, our cousin"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.27,0:09:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Alison, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.99,0:09:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Matron!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:05.08,0:09:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like such a hearty person, \Njust as my cousins described you!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.48,0:09:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness, did you really say that?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.59,0:09:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We still need to check in your luggage, \Nso come to the dorm later.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.92,0:09:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.63,0:09:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Gee, Alison, are you really going \Nto talk to everyone like that? {????? I hear "taraka alison, come on, getting ahead of yourself/carried away/feeling good" - nc what's that taraka}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.83,0:09:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give others such obvious compliments!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.40,0:09:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Flattery will get you everywhere. {lit: there is no person who doesn't like being flattered}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.47,0:09:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, this is our cousin Alison!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.98,0:09:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.44,0:09:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You girls are certainly cousins. \NI can already see a resemblance to Isabel and Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.61,0:09:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:43.18,0:09:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought we aren't much alike.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.72,0:09:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She said we're alike, didn't you hear?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.59,0:09:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless, you're just like I imagined you to be, Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.39,0:09:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're probably \Neven more virtuous than that.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.30,0:09:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad I came to St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.83,0:10:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If that feeling is sincere, \Nplease do your best. {implying she doesn't beleve alison really thinks so}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.87,0:10:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.84,0:10:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison is still as dry as ever \Nand only thinks about herself. {dunno what "dry" implies as a borrowed word in japanese}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.85,0:10:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet she's already thinking a lot of herself. {"feeling good/getting ahead of herself" again}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.30,0:10:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a relief when they didn't put us in the same room today.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.02,0:10:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping an eye on her around the clock \Nwould've been a pain.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.46,0:10:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I just hope it all goes well, that's all.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.98,0:10:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Vous savez, en France il y a beacoup d'artists.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.10,0:10:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Par exemple: poète,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.00,0:10:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,écrivain, peintre. Alors... {unowen: You know, in France there are many artists, for example : poets, writers, painters, then...}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.31,0:10:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My! {assuming}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.69,0:10:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.99,0:10:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, to hell with it!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.58,0:11:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The first day of classes came to a close without any serious incidents, it seems.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.91,0:11:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If only we manage to keep this up... {/I just hope it continues like that forever}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.60,0:11:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Alison, the newcomer?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.98,0:11:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison! {bruh whats with her voice lmao}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.02,0:11:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:23.54,0:11:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Alison, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.22,0:11:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Rita and Katie from the sixth form sent for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.06,0:11:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Go there at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.31,0:11:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm never gonna clean someone's boots!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.70,0:11:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It’ll make my hands dirty, \Nand soap always irritates my skin. {lit: i'm prone to skin rash from soap}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.92,0:11:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't leave the campus \Nwithout a senior's permission.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.45,0:11:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't go down to town!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.42,0:12:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that town we passed through yesterday? {when we came here}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.36,0:12:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I want to go \Nto such a rural town anyway?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.96,0:12:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Suit yourself, then!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.63,0:12:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.24,0:12:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see Pat is still as short-tempered as ever.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.44,0:12:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're still as hell-bent as ever. {lit: person who doesn't understand/obstinate}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.07,0:12:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just a very ordinary girl.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.77,0:12:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, listening to your seniors \Nis the rule of this school, got it?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.45,0:12:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read the school rules, \Nit doesn't say that anywhere.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.53,0:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to—\Nit's been agreed on since forever! {lit: decided since long ago}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.38,0:12:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And who agreed on it? {lit: decided by who?}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.19,0:12:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.42,0:12:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, if that's your final word, \NI wash my hands of it. {lit: if you say so, go alone}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.83,0:12:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to get so overly serious about it. \NJust let me handle this.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.83,0:12:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Off I go now.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.69,0:12:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You've finally finished {writing }it?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.18,0:12:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.24,0:12:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.05,0:13:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.05,0:13:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.76,0:13:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Those cakes look delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.52,0:13:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I have one too?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:09.66,0:13:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Who said they were for you?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.09,0:13:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They are for us—the sixth formers—to eat!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.26,0:13:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re celebrating finishing our homework.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.70,0:13:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, but... What if you leave some over? {meaning "what if you don't eat all of them"}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.33,0:13:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we do, that has nothing to do with you!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.94,0:13:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now go—light up the stove, \Nboil some water, and clean our boots!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.63,0:13:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.81,0:13:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.01,0:13:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to light the stove.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.90,0:13:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.35,0:13:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.44,0:13:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.28,0:13:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You've never done it at home?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.05,0:13:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.05,0:13:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I would sure like to see what kind of parent \Ndoesn't even teach their daughter {\i1}that{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.89,0:13:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying everyone else can do it?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.66,0:13:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.11,0:13:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what's stopping you \Nfrom doing it yourself?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.08,0:13:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.90,0:13:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And here I was, thinking \Nit was actually something important. {lit: i thought you called me for something more important}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.67,0:13:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.49,0:14:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.31,0:14:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Winifred, the head girl.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.68,0:14:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Head girl? So that's why you look \Nso reasonable and smart!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.28,0:14:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the big idea—\Ndisregarding your seniors?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.86,0:14:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it doesn't bother me \Nthat I can't leave the campus. {lit: it's the same to me if I'm forbidden to go out}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.27,0:14:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not all!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.13,0:14:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You might get kicked out of the school \Nfor breaking our long-standing tradition.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.26,0:14:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite all right. \NI'll just come right back in. {lit: it's okay, I can return at once anyway}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.54,0:14:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You really don't understand, do you?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.54,0:14:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That means expulsion! {/you'll get expelled}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.31,0:14:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Expulsion?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.49,0:14:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Understood! \NI'll light the stove at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.72,0:14:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The fire still hasn’t caught?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.48,0:14:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Not at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.63,0:14:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.00,0:15:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you can't start a fire out of nothing! {lit: obviously it's impossible for fire to suddenly catch - meaning there's no paper and sticks, she just tried to light the coals right away}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.60,0:15:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,First you put in some paper \Nand set fire to that!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.19,0:15:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.54,0:15:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness, that Alison...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.84,0:15:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.24,0:15:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Where can I find some paper?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.28,0:15:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see it on that desk?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.68,0:15:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's even in her head...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.67,0:15:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.79,0:15:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My word, where was she brought up, really? {lit: i wonder what discipline; training; teaching manners​}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.72,0:15:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But weren't we like that at first too?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.16,0:15:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's also true, actually.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.84,0:15:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's burning!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.24,0:15:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It burned well!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.64,0:15:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's only natural.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.55,0:15:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Rita?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.10,0:15:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My homework...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.22,0:15:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My homework is on fire!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.07,0:15:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Step back!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.90,0:16:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Your homework?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.20,0:16:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The French homework we're supposed \Nto submit to Mam'zelle tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.19,0:16:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.29,0:16:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How come...?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.31,0:16:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you burn it?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.46,0:16:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But you told me \Nthe paper was on the desk.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.88,0:16:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you to take the newspapers \Nthat were on it! {no you didn't}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.42,0:16:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't you open your eyes for once \Nand check if it was in French or not?! {lit: if you just checked if it had french written on it or not, wouldn't you understand?}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.96,0:16:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison! Apologise!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.99,0:16:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry! \NShe didn't do it on purpose!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.15,0:16:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What's it to me if it was on purpose or not?! {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.03,0:16:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me several days \Nto finally finish that homework...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.52,0:16:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no joke.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.39,0:16:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... And what if we go to Mam'zelle\N and explain the situation?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.88,0:16:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do that!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.89,0:16:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.14,0:16:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.52,0:16:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It is Mam'zelle's policy that you must turn in \Nyour homework by the appointed date,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.19,0:16:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter the circumstances.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.84,0:17:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But... it wouldn't hurt to try! {lit: we'll go anyway}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.09,0:17:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, you're coming with us!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.28,0:17:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand the situation.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.01,0:17:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't just tell Rita that it's okay for her \Nnot to turn in her homework.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.40,0:17:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect her homework \Non my desk tomorrow, as arranged.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.14,0:17:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's hopeless... {/after all}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.77,0:17:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What's hopeless?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.14,0:17:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We had hoped that you \Nwouldn't be quite as strict today...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.40,0:17:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it took Rita days to finish that homework, \Nthere's no way she can redo it all by tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.88,0:17:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! It wouldn't be possible!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.48,0:17:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... What would happen \Nif she doesn't submit it?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:37.17,0:17:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Rita wouldn't be able to graduate.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.61,0:17:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.79,0:17:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't be able to graduate?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.56,0:17:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I don't believe it would come to that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.03,0:17:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.97,0:17:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She can't finish it by tomorrow, can she?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.22,0:17:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Our school has something we call \N"The Spirit of St. Clare's."
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.68,0:17:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The Spirit of St. Clare's?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.16,0:18:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll understand soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.94,0:18:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, just sit back and watch.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.66,0:18:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe what Alison has done.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.69,0:18:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,True. That won't just blow off. {lit: really, we're really in trouble}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:16.10,0:18:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think that Spirit of St. Clare's that Mam'zelle told us about could be?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.37,0:18:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.14,0:18:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna go and see how it goes?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.21,0:18:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now? {lit: go out?}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.84,0:18:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.65,0:18:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all helping Rita with her homework!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.66,0:18:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we bring them a midnight snack?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.34,0:18:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, let's do that.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.13,0:18:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Matron!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.90,0:18:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's us!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.97,0:18:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A snack for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.00,0:18:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Please help yourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.90,0:19:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,While the tea is still hot.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.74,0:19:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take you up on that.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.68,0:19:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. \NThat snack was great.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.38,0:19:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You girls can return to your dorm now.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.72,0:19:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.92,0:19:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me stay here.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.79,0:19:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too. {/please}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.60,0:19:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hopeless!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.02,0:19:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you say that? \NWe still have three hours left.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.22,0:19:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.55,0:19:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't possibly finish this without a map \Nof 19th century downtown Paris at hand!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.56,0:19:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.49,0:19:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,On that, I wrote down all the cafes \Nand avenues that Musset frequented. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfred_de_Musset}{/walking paths}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.96,0:20:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They are essential for a thorough study \Nof Musset’s youth.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.47,0:20:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Musset... You mean the French poet?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.47,0:20:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The subject of Rita’s homework \Nis the life of Musset,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.64,0:20:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the four great Romantic poets \Nand the author of the play {\i1}No Trifling with Love{\i0}. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfred_de_Musset#Plays - not sure what the correct english title would be}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.48,0:20:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We could recover everything else from memory, \Nbut without that map with Rita’s markings… {lit: others things taught, only the map on which rita wrote...}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:18.02,0:20:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as we're so close to finishing it...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.12,0:20:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, sure you can't recall it?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.26,0:20:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also included a couple \Nof Musset's unique private poems,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.33,0:20:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's now lost too. {????? lit: poems that musset wrote on special permission; license; licence; concession; charter - dunno what it means, maybe that he couldn't publish them? how did she find them then? why does she say they're unrecoverable now}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.09,0:20:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't find that...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.91,0:20:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.06,0:20:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here? {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.91,0:20:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all I could recover... {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.41,0:20:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that just some burned scraps? {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.53,0:20:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of the homework.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.12,0:20:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But maybe you can still read something \Nthat was written on it. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.02,0:20:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that maybe \Nit could be of use to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.77,0:21:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.80,0:21:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The map I used!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.09,0:21:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.71,0:21:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.74,0:21:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Alison.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.56,0:21:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Finished it
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.36,0:21:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.67,0:21:47.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,Well now, Rita. \NIt seems you've done it, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:01.57,0:22:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone's in trouble,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.96,0:22:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone will help her out.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.93,0:22:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the Spirit of St. Clare's!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:35.41,0:23:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The school lacrosse tournament \Nwill be held in a week.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.82,0:23:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But Joan says she won't come out on the field!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:40.74,0:23:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone must participate!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.22,0:23:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just Joan—it doesn't seem like anyone is taking it seriously.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:45.69,0:23:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we can kiss victory goodbye. {/winning is impossible}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:47.36,0:23:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We've never given up before, \Nso to hell with starting now!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.66,0:23:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the plan: I'll give personal \Nspecial training to Joan.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.20,0:23:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But then a terrible incident struck!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.33,0:23:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Joan fell off the balance beam \Nand got hurt badly.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.10,0:23:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.87,0:24:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Lovely Miss Roberts."
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.26,0:24:03.69,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 15 \NThe Lovely Miss Roberts {素敵なロバート先生}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.34,0:24:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
